node.text: Have you ever tried to make anything from concrete? As for me?...Let’s just say that cement and I would not have been seat mates on the school bus. I have had lots of successes with cement but if you leave with one tip of the day from this diy...know that you should NEVER use “cement all” quick set when trying to shove cement into pantyhose and tie it up with rubber bands unless you work like a cheetah sprinting while on steroids. The Pinterest girls made it looks so easy. 🤔 I did actually have 3 that turned out...one even being out of the “cement all”. 😱I guess I might be part cheetah. #diyconcrete #concretepumpkin #diygonewrong

node.text: After six years of stripping, sanding, and crack picking, it’s finished! What do you think?! Are you surprised that I decided to use the old knobs? Did you think I would end up painting it? Since it won’t fit through any of our doors to get it inside, we are just going to hang out here in our new outdoor living room and sniff the mountain air while listening to the neighbor dogs. I couldn’t be happier with the way that it turned out and I’m so excited to use this in our new kitchen when we build for towels, utensils, and all the things! Oh and if you ever paint any cabinets blue, I will come for you. Oh, and I love you! 😘 #mapcabinet #printerscabinet #drawers #ididit

node.text: Did you vote “neigh🐴 ” on my candle holders at the thrift store? I love them! ♥️🍁 #brasscandleholder #brass #glasstobrass #candles

node.text: I’m still alive, although I’ve been sitting on the couch for a couple hours waiting to see if I’m dying…note taken…don’t use bleach and vinegar together. Oh, and I sprayed bleach all over my rug so if I come out in the morning and it’s in pieces, at least it will be easier to get in the trash. 😊 I couldn’t find a way to get the fuzz off or it wouldn’t have been a project fail. 😩 It looks so cool bleached under there, but the fuzz is making it not 😎! I needed it trimmed to the time bare bones and it was just taking FOREVER with the skiver and nothing else was working…sanding, hair trimmers, sheep shears, tried it all. We can have a cremation ceremony in the morning…unless the fuzz surprises me and the bleach doesn’t eat it alive.🤞 #livingroomdecor #mood

node.text: Swipe for the “before” Did you see the gumball machine turned dog treat machine? Chester sure loves it! I made him one a while back that has a stand on it. I found another at a thrift store for $10 and it was screaming treat machine too! All the details, what kind of treats we use in it, what colors I used, etc…on the blog in profile. Would you use one of these for pet treats too? Your pet will thank you if you do! #gumballmachine #vintagegumballmachine #dogtreats #dogsofinstagram #goldendoodlesofinstagram

node.text: Did you see my cabinet wonderings in stories? I thought maybe painting the inside a taupe color instead of white might be an option too. 🤔 Or, I might just wait until we move and see what I think in our new house. Wonderings. If the squirrel 🐿 hadn’t brought me wax to my door today, this wouldn’t be a wondering. I’mstill planning on using that wax on something else so it’s not a waste if I leave this cabinet. It gave me an excuse to sit here and stare into the abyss today. 😁 Now I’m going to lie down and stare to give my behind a break. Happy weekend, friends!!! #home #homedecor

node.text: Chester was in the 50% that liked the quilt. 😂♥️ Do you have a fave find from a thrift store? Mine would have to be one of my cabinets for sure. This cabinet, chair, mirror (behind the chair), nightstand, lamp, and mirror on the nightstand are all second hand finds or thrifted and then refurbished or diyed. 🙌🏼 I wish I knew where this quilt was from so I could get a king size in it…so if you’ve seen it somewhere, let me know. 😁 #thriftstorefinds #rustic #antique #vintage
